# `Assertible` To `Junit`
[![](https://img.shields.io/badge/Assertible-white.svg?style=for-the-badge&logo=data:image/png;base64,)]()  [![](https://img.shields.io/badge/JUnit-gray.svg?style=for-the-badge&logo=data:image/png;base64,)]()

Most of the CI tools already have an extension to generate a `JUnit` report based on `xml` result, this tool transforms `json` to `xml`.

Input:
- `results.json`    JSON that contains the test run results of assertible
- `tests.json`      JSON that contains tests' details stored in assertible

Install:
```sh
npm i -g assertible-to-junit
```

Run:
```sh
assertible-to-junit "$(cat results.json)" "$(cat tests.json)"
```
